word_mean_info__list.difference: 指特许或恩施的权利，也指一般人或物所没有的有利条件。
普通用词，指某人或某物拥有符合法律、道义或道德的权利。

word_group.brief_definition: 男性特权；男子特权；男人特权
医患特权；医生 - 病人特权

bilingual.target: 不是每个人都有这种特权。

bilingual.source: It is an honor to have such a privilege.
bilingual.target: 拥有这种特权是一种荣幸。

bilingual.source: He has the privilege of accessing this club.
bilingual.target: 他有进入这个俱乐部的特权。

bilingual.source: The CEO has the privilege of using the company jet.
bilingual.target: 首席执行官有使用公司飞机的特权。

bilingual.source: Having a car in the city is considered a privilege.
bilingual.target: 在城市里拥有一辆车被认为是一种特权。

bilingual.source: Access to the VIP lounge is a privilege for first-class passengers.
bilingual.target: 进入贵宾休息室是头等舱乘客的特权。

bilingual.source: She felt it was a privilege to be invited to the exclusive event.
bilingual.target: 她觉得被邀请参加这个独家活动是一种特权。

bilingual.source: He used his privilege to get a better seat at the concert.
bilingual.target: 他利用他的特权在音乐会上得到了一个更好的座位。

bilingual.source: This can give white middle-class children a sense of superiority or privilege.
bilingual.target: 这可以给白人中产阶级的孩子一种优越感或特权感。

list.abstract: privilege是一个英语单词，名词、动词，作名词时意思是“特权；优待”，作及物动词时意思是“给予…特权；特免”。
Privilege，网络流行语。privilege的英文翻译为特殊利益、优惠待遇，因一位微博用户的一段“privilege”式发言在微博火出圈。

yingyinNormal.en: But it would mean breaking attorney-client privilege.
yingyinNormal.zh: 也就是要我打破律师与当事人保密特权。

yingyinNormal.en: If I were to waive privilege, what would your testimony be?
yingyinNormal.zh: 如果我放弃特权你的证词会说什么？

yingyinNormal.en: You don't have to lie to me. You're covered by attorney-client privilege.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你不必对我说假话，你受律师与当事人保密特权保护。

yingyinNormal.en: As you are aware, we have invoked the State secrets privilege during our request for dismissal.
yingyinNormal.zh: 正如您所知，在要求撤诉时，我们援引了国家机密特权。

yingyinNormal.en: No. You have no attorney-client privilege. Everybody else is a lawyer. The world is full of lawyers.
yingyinNormal.zh: 不想。你没有律师委托人保密特权，其他人都是律师，满世界都是律师。

yingyinNormal.en: Marilyn. Yes, Mr. Governor? I have instructed Mr. Gardner not to waive my attorney client privilege.
yingyinNormal.zh: 玛丽莲。我在，州长先生。我已经告诉加德纳先生不放弃我的律师与当事人保密特权。

yingyinNormal.en: It's open. Marilyn. What do you need? Sir, I need you to waive attorney-client privilege so Mr. Gardner can answer my questions.
yingyinNormal.zh: 门开着，玛丽莲，有什么事？先生，我需要你放弃律师当事人保密特权，让加德纳先生回答我的问题。

yingyinNormal.en: Rajesh, I've had the privilege of working alongside you for many years.
yingyinNormal.zh: 拉杰，我有幸跟你一起共事了多年。

yingyinNormal.en: This little circle of light, it's part of me now, not just armor. It's a terrible privilege.
yingyinNormal.zh: 这个小光环已经是我的一部分了，它不仅是护甲，是一种可怕的恩赐。

yingyinNormal.en: Judy, it is my great privilege to officially assign you to the heart of Zootopia, Precinct One. City Center.
yingyinNormal.zh: 朱迪，我很荣幸地将你分配到动物城的中心一区，市中心。

yingyinNormal.en: Again, I want you to know that attorney-client privilege covers all his dealings with you. Not illegal dealings.
yingyinNormal.zh: 此外，我希望你知道律师当事人保密协议涵盖了他与你之间所有的事务。不包括非法事务。

yingyinNormal.en: What? Why ever not? My Lady, we're both honoured to be allowed the privilege... No. I want to hear from Mrs Hughes.
yingyinNormal.zh: 什么？为什么不愿意？夫人，我们都很荣幸能够...不，我想听休斯太太自己的意见。

yingyinNormal.en: Do I get a say in this? Today, we are soldiers. Soldiers die for their country. I regret, Dr Watson, that privilege is now yours.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我有发言权吗？今天我们是士兵，士兵为国捐躯。很遗憾，华生医生，这荣幸属于你了。

yingyinNormal.en: I had the privilege of knowing a small town girl from the scene in District 12, who survived the Hunger Games and the Quarter Quell.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我有幸知道一位来自十二区的小镇姑娘，如何在饥饿游戏和世纪极限赛中存活下来。

yingyinNormal.en: I have got the privilege of being on one of the floats tonight. Yes. What advice would you give me? Make sure you don't fall off and enjoy!
yingyinNormal.zh: 今晚我很荣幸能获准登上游行彩车。是的。你会给我些什么建议呢？确保别摔下来，然后就是尽情享受啦。

yingyinNormal.en: Ted Hendricks. Managing director of the transition. Never fun, this stage. But we do have ahead of us the privilege of publishing what will be the very last issue of LIFE magazine.
yingyinNormal.zh: 泰德·亨德里克斯，过渡期主任。这个阶段一点都不有趣，现今我们最重要的一件事，就是我们最后一期的生活周刊特辑。

yingyinNormal.en: I am not going to be a spectator this evening, I am actually going to be part of the parade itself and I have the privilege of riding the Hong Kong Tourism Board Float and here she is.
yingyinNormal.zh: 今晚我不只是观众，事实上我本人也是游行的一份子，而且我还荣获特许能搭乘上香港旅游局的彩车，就是这辆。

direction_info.description:
数据源自2012-2023年12年间全国考研试卷，由搜狗翻译进行大数据分析汇总，数据仅供参考。

<highlight> 考频分布</highlight>
由搜狗翻译收集历年真题试卷、汇总单词出现的总频次、释义分布。题型选自2012-2023年全国考研英语一和考研英语二共24套考研试卷，包括阅读、完型填空、翻译、写作等所有题型。

<highlight> 考纲释义</highlight>
精选全国考研考纲词汇、单词义项，由搜狗大数据与考纲、历年真题进行匹配。

<highlight>真题例句</highlight>
精选2012-2023年12年间全国考研英语一和考研英语二试卷，由搜狗大数据与搜索内容匹配历年真题例句。

搜狗翻译拥有最终解释权。

examination_example.sentence: High school graduates are entitled to more educational <highlight>privileges</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 高中毕业生有权利获得更多的教育特权。

examination_example.sentence: These are the kind of workers that countries like Britain, Canada and Australia try to attract by using immigration rules that <highlight>privilege</highlight> college graduates.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 英国、加拿大和澳大利亚等国试图利用赋予大学毕业生特权的移民规定来吸引这类工人。
